bib.title: Elastic and inelastic scattering of alpha particlesfrom 40,44Ca over a broad range of energies and angles.

free_txt: The detection system consisted of seven
detectors cooled to about -20 degr.These detectors are
placed 10 degr.apart on a turntable rotatable around
the target axis.
The errors on the data points are statistical
only
Errors of the absolute cross sections
Digitizing error
Digitizing error
The beam intensity was adjusted to get deadtime
corrections less than 10%.
The energy spread of the beam is of the order of 0.3%.
The size of the beam spot on the target is 3*3 mm.
The accuracy of the detection angles was checked by
Rutherford scattering on both sides of the beam axis
and was found to be accurate to +-0.2 degr.The solid
angles were measured by Rutherford scattering of 15 MeV
alpha particles from a thin gold target and were found
to agree with the geometrical estimate.
Self-supporting targets of isotopically pure 40Ca and
44Ca  located in the center of a 1 m diameter
scattering chamber were used. All targets contained
some carbon (0.21 mg/cm2) and oxygen (0.26 mg/cm2).
The target thickness was 0.78 mg/cm2.
